text: Emberá-Wounaan is an indigenous region of Panama. The population is of 9 544 habitants (2010) and the area is of 4 383,5 km²; was created in 1983. The capital is Unión Chocó. Emberá-Wounaan has 2 districts and 5 corregimientos: Districts Corregimientos Capital of the district Cémaco Cirilo Guaynora, Lajas Blancas, Manuel Ortega Unión Chocó Sambú Jingurundó, Río Sabalo Puerto Indio Category:Comarcas of Panama
title: Emberá-Wounaan Comarca
